TITLE: Main Entry Point Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Main execution logic and entry point for the MCP client application.
SOURCE: https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/modelcontextprotocol/blob/main/docs/tutorials/building-a-client-node.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Main execution
async function main() {
  if (process.argv.length < 3) {
    console.log("Usage: ts-node client.ts <path_to_server_script>");
    process.exit(1);
  }

  const client = new MCPClient();
  try {
    await client.connectToServer(process.argv[2]);
    await client.chatLoop();
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error:", error);
    await client.cleanup();
    process.exit(1);
  }
}

// Run main if this is the main module
if (import.meta.url === new URL(process.argv[1], "file:").href) {
  main();
}

export default MCPClient;
```

