TITLE: Implementing Tools in TypeScript MCP Server
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to implement a basic tool (calculate_sum) in a TypeScript MCP server, including tool definition and execution handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/modelcontextprotocol/blob/main/docs/docs/concepts/tools.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const server = new Server({
  name: "example-server",
  version: "1.0.0"
}, {
  capabilities: {
    tools: {}
  }
});

// Define available tools
server.setRequestHandler(ListToolsRequestSchema, async () => {
  return {
    tools: [{
      name: "calculate_sum",
      description: "Add two numbers together",
      inputSchema: {
        type: "object",
        properties: {
          a: { type: "number" },
          b: { type: "number" }
        },
        required: ["a", "b"]
      }
    }]
  };
});

// Handle tool execution
server.setRequestHandler(CallToolRequestSchema, async (request) => {
  if (request.params.name === "calculate_sum") {
    const { a, b } = request.params.arguments;
    return {
      content: [
        {
          type: "text",
          text: String(a + b)
        }
      ]
    };
  }
  throw new Error("Tool not found");
});
```

